{"id":14881762,"mediaExerciseId":"f8ea0464-7797-427c-a01b-074c16ba668c","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612470,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":735,"solutions":[{"id":5978720,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine which option best describes a Yankee bond.\n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/2642787d063c349d0d95e07ec0647030/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/2642787d063c349d0d95e07ec0647030/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Foreign bonds** are issued in a *single currency* and usually denominated in that *country's currency*. They are often nicknamed for the country where the foreign bond is issued. **Yankee bonds** are foreign bonds issued in the *United States*.\n\n\nLet us analyze and determine the best option that describes the Yankee bond.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":212,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/671cb4deb3951d97baf4b6c441d73ce9/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":107,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/671cb4deb3951d97baf4b6c441d73ce9/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"a) The bond issued by General Motors in Japan with the interest payable in U.S. dollars. It is **not a Yankee bond** since it is *issued in a foreign country* even if the bond's interest is payable in U.S. dollars.\n\n*Therefore, answer a is not correct.*","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/ded324983d40e55f63f6f0b345148a90/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/ded324983d40e55f63f6f0b345148a90/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"b) A bond issued by General Motors in Japan with the interest payable in yen. It is **not a Yankee bond** since the bond is *issued in a foreign country* and the *interest is also payable in Japanese Yen*.\n\n*Therefore, answer b is not correct.*","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/99e98ca6ec5143fb1b3202dd38ce8e1d/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/99e98ca6ec5143fb1b3202dd38ce8e1d/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"c) A bond issued by Toyota in the United States with the interest payable in yen. It is **not a Yankee bond** since the *interest is payable is Japanese Yen* even if the bond is issued in the United States.\n\n*Therefore, answer c is not correct.*","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/636536e862b4a83e0deca7ec336819bd/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/636536e862b4a83e0deca7ec336819bd/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"e)  A bond issued by Toyota worldwide with the interest payable in dollars. It is **not a Yankee bond** since it should be *issued and traded only in United States*.\n\n*Therefore, answer e is not correct.*","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/ac183eb298bdf2ae8114b32ba2024fd4/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/ac183eb298bdf2ae8114b32ba2024fd4/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"d) A bond issued by Toyota in the United States with the interest payable in dollars. It is **a Yankee bond** since it is issued in United States and the interest is payable in U.S. dollars.\n\n**Therefore, answer d is correct.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/5eccb0eab75d8d07492cbc40d6d5a44e/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/15c25e378c5bf9c384117bb2f73bc618/5eccb0eab75d8d07492cbc40d6d5a44e/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"57a153d1-9578-44ad-ae1c-91704a58a3ea","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeI